spectre_timerfree.c

Timer-free variant: software-counter thread replaces rdcycle/rdtime.


On the board: Spectre v1 — T-Head XuanTie C910 (BeagleV-Ahead board)

gcc -O1 -DC910 -march=rv64gc -o spectre_timerfree spectre_timerfree.c -lpthread


For gem5:

Use full system simulation. script provided (riscv-fs.py)

/opt/riscv/bin/riscv64-unknown-linux-gnu-gcc -march=rv64gc_zicbom_zicbop -o spectre_timerfree spectre_timerfree.c -lpthread


Pin the attack thread to hart-0 and the counter thread to hart-1:

taskset -c 0 ./spectre_timerfree


Installing RISC-V Toolchain
To cross-compile C code for a RISC-V target, you will need to use the RISC-V toolchain.

$ sudo apt-get install autoconf automake autotools-dev curl python3 python3-pip libmpc-dev libmpfr-dev libgmp-dev gawk build-essential bison flex texinfo gperf libtool patchutils bc zlib1g-dev libexpat-dev ninja-build git cmake libglib2.0-dev libslirp-dev
$ git clone https://github.com/riscv/riscv-gnu-toolchain
$ cd riscv-gnu-toolchain/
$ ./configure --prefix=/opt/riscv
$ sudo make linux 


Installing Gem5 Toolchain
To install the GEM5 toolchain, execute the following commands:

$ sudo apt install build-essential git m4 scons zlib1g zlib1g-dev     libprotobuf-dev protobuf-compiler libprotoc-dev libgoogle-perftools-dev     python3-dev libboost-all-dev pkg-config python3-tk
$ git clone https://github.com/gem5/gem5.git
$ cd gem5/
$ scons build/RISCV/gem5.opt -j8



